tml#termIfThenElse","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L157-L157","name":"«termIfLet_:=_Then_Else_»","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/13549422513598363237.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#«termIfLet_:=_Then_Else_»","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L160-L162","name":"boolIfThenElse","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/16438345948611871623.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#boolIfThenElse","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L167-L167","name":"«term_<|_»","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/3686517455255254057.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#«term_<|_»","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L173-L173","name":"«term_|>_»","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/14965443893308830333.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#«term_|>_»","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L181-L181","name":"«term_$__»","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/9153583048747386411.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#«term_$__»","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L187-L187","name":"«term{__:_//_}»","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/13322025255768013403.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#«term{__:_//_}»","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L197-L197","name":"termWithout_expected_type_","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/18427813203610603865.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#termWithout_expected_type_","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L199-L199","name":"«term[_]»","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/11776945680615234273.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#«term[_]»","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L200-L200","name":"«term%[_|_]»","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/10251732395297030121.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#«term%[_|_]»","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L216-L216","name":"Lean.term_Matches_","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/4634910716411695147.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.term_Matches_","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L220-L221","name":"Lean.termThis","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/13009554918307031915.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.termThis","doc":"Special identifier introduced by \"anonymous\" `have : ...`, `suffices p ...` etc. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L224-L242","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.intro","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/17402865129139278309.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.intro","doc":"Introduce one or more hypotheses, optionally naming and/or pattern-matching them.\nFor each hypothesis to be introduced, the remaining main goal's target type must be a `let` or function type.\n* `intro` by itself introduces one anonymous hypothesis, which can be accessed by e.g. `assumption`.\n* `intro x y` introduces two hypotheses and names them. Individual hypotheses can be anonymized via `_`,\n  or matched against a pattern:\n  ```lean\n  -- ... ⊢ α × β → ...\n  intro (a, b)\n  -- ..., a : α, b : β ⊢ ...\n  ```\n* Alternatively, `intro` can be combined with pattern matching much like `fun`:\n  ```lean\n  intro\n  | n + 1, 0 => tac\n  | ...\n  ```\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L243-L244","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.intros","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/14221804682197426433.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.intros","doc":"`intros x...` behaves like `intro x...`, but then keeps introducing (anonymous) hypotheses until goal is not of a function type. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L245-L248","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.rename","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/4475571077697689127.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.rename","doc":"`rename t => x` renames the most recent hypothesis whose type matches `t` (which may contain placeholders) to `x`,\nor fails if no such hypothesis could be found. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L249-L250","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.revert","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/6633503797509847769.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.revert","doc":"`revert x...` is the inverse of `intro x...`: it moves the given hypotheses into the main goal's target type. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L251-L252","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.clear","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/4788007406659257775.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.clear","doc":"`clear x...` removes the given hypotheses, or fails if there are remaining references to a hypothesis. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L253-L256","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.subst","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/10886185670068869033.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.subst","doc":"`subst x...` substitutes each `x` with `e` in the goal if there is a hypothesis of type `x = e` or `e = x`.\nIf `x` is itself a hypothesis of type `y = e` or `e = y`, `y` is substituted instead. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L257-L260","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.assumption","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/5471390806776695527.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.assumption","doc":"`assumption` tries to solve the main goal using a hypothesis of compatible type, or else fails.\nNote also the `‹t›` term notation, which is a shorthand for `show t by assumption`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L261-L271","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.contradiction","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/4710949832259743233.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.contradiction","doc":"`contradiction` closes the main goal if its hypotheses are \"trivially contradictory\".\n```lean\nexample (h : False) : p := by contradiction  -- inductive type/family with no applicable constructors\nexample (h : none = some true) : p := by contradiction  -- injectivity of constructors\nexample (h : 2 + 2 = 3) : p := by contradiction  -- decidable false proposition\nexample (h : p) (h' : ¬ p) : q := by contradiction\nexample (x : Nat) (h : x ≠ x) : p := by contradiction\n```\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L272-L280","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.apply","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/10233995239623531853.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.apply","doc":"`apply e` tries to match the current goal against the conclusion of `e`'s type.\nIf it succeeds, then the tactic returns as many subgoals as the number of premises that\nhave not been fixed by type inference or type class resolution.\nNon-dependent premises are added before dependent ones.\n\nThe `apply` tactic uses higher-order pattern matching, type class resolution, and first-order unification with dependent types.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L281-L284","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.exact","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/12613814261787041117.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.exact","doc":"`exact e` closes the main goal if its target type matches that of `e`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L285-L289","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.refine","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/17522448694755385543.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.refine","doc":"`refine e` behaves like `exact e`, except that named (`?x`) or unnamed (`?_`) holes in `e` that are not solved\nby unification with the main goal's target type are converted into new goals, using the hole's name, if any, as the goal case name.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L290-L291","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.refine'","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/842689916303204677.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.refine'","doc":"`refine' e` behaves like `refine e`, except that unsolved placeholders (`_`) and implicit parameters are also converted into new goals. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L292-L293","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.constructor","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/15599055256032349579.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.constructor","doc":"If the main goal's target type is an inductive type, `constructor` solves it with the first matching constructor, or else fails. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L294-L297","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.case","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/6053691362389903795.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.case","doc":"`case tag => tac` focuses on the goal with case name `tag` and solves it using `tac`, or else fails.\n`case tag x₁ ... xₙ => tac` additionally renames the `n` most recent hypotheses with inaccessible names to the given names. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L298-L301","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.«tacticNext___=>_»","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/10640352880538208211.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.«tacticNext___=>_»","doc":"`next => tac` focuses on the next goal solves it using `tac`, or else fails.\n`next x₁ ... xₙ => tac` additionally renames the `n` most recent hypotheses with inaccessible names to the given names. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L303-L304","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.allGoals","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/6145825727778322419.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.allGoals","doc":"`allGoals tac` runs `tac` on each goal, concatenating the resulting goals, if any. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L305-L306","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.anyGoals","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/15174319498215257985.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.anyGoals","doc":"`anyGoals tac` applies the tactic `tac` to every goal, and succeeds if at least one application succeeds.  "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L307-L310","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.focus","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/7130736660569328821.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.focus","doc":"`focus tac` focuses on the main goal, suppressing all other goals, and runs `tac` on it.\nUsually `· tac`, which enforces that the goal is closed by `tac`, should be preferred. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L311-L312","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.skip","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/16848977032227284721.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.skip","doc":"`skip` does nothing. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L313-L314","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.done","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/14155599149755222065.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.done","doc":"`done` succeeds iff there are no remaining goals. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L315-L315","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.traceState","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/17122479126477242025.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.traceState","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L316-L316","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.traceMessage","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/943287481980766047.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.traceMessage","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L317-L317","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.failIfSuccess","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/10275941755935439003.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.failIfSuccess","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L318-L318","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.paren","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/17393560597314129521.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.paren","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L319-L319","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.withReducible","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/15263123838593183357.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.withReducible","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L320-L320","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.withReducibleAndInstances","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/13722797373677586123.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.withReducibleAndInstances","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L321-L322","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.first","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/427876026619100709.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.first","doc":"`first | tac | ...` runs each `tac` until one succeeds, or else fails. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L323-L323","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.rotateLeft","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/7345352141083943007.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.rotateLeft","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L324-L324","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.rotateRight","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/17140577128441892545.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.rotateRight","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L325-L326","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticTry_","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/14262516925126399471.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticTry_","doc":"`try tac` runs `tac` and succeeds even if `tac` failed. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L327-L328","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.«tactic_<;>_»","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/16473879056817549341.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.«tactic_<;>_»","doc":"`tac <;> tac'` runs `tac` on the main goal and `tac'` on each produced goal, concatenating all goals produced by `tac'`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L330-L331","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticRfl","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/900050247022513773.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticRfl","doc":"`rfl` is a shorthand for `exact rfl`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L332-L333","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticAdmit","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/6978892680042399241.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticAdmit","doc":"`admit` is a shorthand for `exact sorry`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L334-L335","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticSorry","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/12972049151286018015.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticSorry","doc":"The `sorry` tactic is a shorthand for `exact sorry`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L336-L336","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticInfer_instance","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/10417222844760313453.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticInfer_instance","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L338-L339","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.config","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/3140477293059881579.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.config","doc":"Optional configuration option for tactics "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L341-L341","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.locationWildcard","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/8686668078641602253.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.locationWildcard","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L342-L342","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.locationHyp","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/17459380237696960367.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.locationHyp","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L343-L343","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.location","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/9029872655426014641.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Notation.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.location","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Notation.lean#L