d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1303-L1307","name":"Monad","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/12547373301970222381.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#Monad","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1309-L1310","name":"instInhabitedForAll_2","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/17668998503976105273.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#instInhabitedForAll_2","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1312-L1313","name":"instInhabited","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/15162211161045186643.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#instInhabited","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1316-L1324","name":"Array.sequenceMap","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/15489152827786200339.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#Array.sequenceMap","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1317-L1323","name":"Array.sequenceMap.loop","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/15107992794036417129.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#Array.sequenceMap.loop","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1330-L1331","name":"MonadLift","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/9736395559119202625.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#MonadLift","doc":"A Function for lifting a computation from an inner Monad to an outer Monad.\n    Like [MonadTrans](https://hackage.haskell.org/package/transformers-0.5.5.0/docs/Control-Monad-Trans-Class.html),\n    but `n` does not have to be a monad transformer.\n    Alternatively, an implementation of [MonadLayer](https://hackage.haskell.org/package/layers-0.1/docs/Control-Monad-Layer.html#t:MonadLayer) without `layerInvmap` (so far). "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1336-L1337","name":"MonadLiftT","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/381548746434395927.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#MonadLiftT","doc":"The reflexive-transitive closure of `MonadLift`.\n    `monadLift` is used to transitively lift monadic computations such as `StateT.get` or `StateT.put s`.\n    Corresponds to [MonadLift](https://hackage.haskell.org/package/layers-0.1/docs/Control-Monad-Layer.html#t:MonadLift). "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1341-L1341","name":"liftM","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/12987064245804869883.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#liftM","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1343-L1344","name":"instMonadLiftT","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/14917147452098304751.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#instMonadLiftT","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1346-L1347","name":"instMonadLiftT_1","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/10798640905719535235.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#instMonadLiftT_1","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1353-L1354","name":"MonadFunctor","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/4687755728117868401.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#MonadFunctor","doc":"A functor in the category of monads. Can be used to lift monad-transforming functions.\n    Based on pipes' [MFunctor](https://hackage.haskell.org/package/pipes-2.4.0/docs/Control-MFunctor.html),\n    but not restricted to monad transformers.\n    Alternatively, an implementation of [MonadTransFunctor](http://duairc.netsoc.ie/layers-docs/Control-Monad-Layer.html#t:MonadTransFunctor). "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1358-L1359","name":"MonadFunctorT","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/18123828958563075195.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#MonadFunctorT","doc":"The reflexive-transitive closure of `MonadFunctor`.\n    `monadMap` is used to transitively lift Monad morphisms "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1363-L1364","name":"instMonadFunctorT","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/1036508886540296635.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#instMonadFunctorT","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1366-L1367","name":"monadFunctorRefl","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/4836349580557958813.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#monadFunctorRefl","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1369-L1371","name":"Except","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/15997936915438629699.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#Except","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1375-L1376","name":"instInhabitedExcept","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/10432223526081493177.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#instInhabitedExcept","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1379-L1381","name":"MonadExceptOf","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/14901874458683113123.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#MonadExceptOf","doc":"An implementation of [MonadError](https://hackage.haskell.org/package/mtl-2.2.2/docs/Control-Monad-Except.html#t:MonadError) "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1383-L1384","name":"throwThe","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/9586951218528766351.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#throwThe","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1386-L1387","name":"tryCatchThe","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/12303949411325939583.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#tryCatchThe","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1390-L1392","name":"MonadExcept","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/4432101628009795677.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#MonadExcept","doc":"Similar to `MonadExceptOf`, but `ε` is an outParam for convenience "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1396-L1398","name":"instMonadExcept","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/5067230567468901169.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#instMonadExcept","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1403-L1404","name":"MonadExcept.orElse","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/10022450353203115407.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#MonadExcept.orElse","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a/src/Init/Prelude.lean#L1406-L1407","name":"MonadExcept.instOrElse","link":"/LeanColls/docs/semantic/11060003731656798665.xml#","docLink":"/LeanColls/docs/Init/Prelude.html#MonadExcept.instOrElse","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/dca5da6b18d95ba75a16d5bcfb81fcb26705709a